			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64589483"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64589483"><p>Staff cutting is never going to be a win for a company. You have multiple choices:<br>a) Do something people don't like hoping they will quit - the people quitting may skew to those with better skills.<br>b) Implement a voluntary redundancy scheme - the people quitting may skew to those with better skills.<br>c) Create a complicated re-org scheme while culling the weak - this costs a lot of money, and is upsetting to the business operations resulting in mass inefficiency for years to come.<br>d) Cull the weak directly by a<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64589483">

